`claimReward()` confirms the root cause: reward routing comes from `referral.getRelationsREF(_wallet)`, and transfers go straight to whatever addresses that contract returns. The existing PoC still lets Barley’s old referral contract decide the recipient on the profitable claim path, so I’m checking the live referral semantics and test flow to make the seized contract actually receive or forward the payout to the verifier.
